http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Kochi/40-new-garbage-bins-for-South-railway-station/article13977699.ece

The Jan Kalyan Society handed over 40 big garbage bins to be placed at Ernakulam Junction Railway Station on Saturday.Speaking on the occasion, Ernakulam Area Manager of Southern Railway Rajesh Chandran said that key railway stations in the city need a few hundred garbage bins, to ensure cleanliness and hygiene. Station Master V Rohit was among those present.The society is a conclave of people from northern India who reside in Kochi. It has been building toilets in schools and also handing over study materials to schoolchildren. Food and clothes were given in many orphanages.